{
  "number": 6849,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/6849",
  "title": "[HIGH SEVERITY VULNERABILITY] `instantsearch.js` should use `qs@^6.14.1` instead of `^6.5.1 < 6.10`",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nCurrently, in `packages/instantsearch.js/package.json`, there is:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"qs\": \"^6.5.1 < 6.10\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nBut with `qs <6.14.1`, there's a high severity vulnerability:\n[qs's arrayLimit bypass in its bracket notation allows DoS via memory exhaustion](https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-6rw7-vpxm-498p)\n\nThis vulnerability was fixed in patched version `6.14.1`.\n\nI hope there's no reason to have `< 6.10`.\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\nWhen installing:\n- `react-instantsearch@latest` _(currently `7.22.0`)_\n- or `instantsearch.js@latest` _(currently `4.86.0`)_\n\n`npm i` or `npm audit` will display the high severity vulnerabilities in the console.\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/github/algolia/instantsearch/tree/templates/react-instantsearch\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\n- No `high severity vulnerabilities` should appear in the console when installing `react-instantsearch@latest`\n- In instantsearch.js `package.json`, there should be: `\"qs\": \"^6.14.1\"`\n\n### Package version\n\n`instantsearch.js@4.86.0` _(via `react-instantsearch@7.22.0`)_\n\n### Operating system\n\n_No response_\n\n### Browser\n\n_No response_\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [x] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
